mutant: m003_merge_cursor_no_advance
target: internal/ingest/orchestrator/merge_runner.go
failure-mode: |
  The merge source cursor commits sf.Idx instead of sf.Idx+1, so a merge
  restart re-processes the just-completed source segment and re-appends its
  events to the destination. Models an off-by-one when deciding whether a
  cursor records "last done" vs "next to do".
expected-detection: |
  On restart the duplicated events should trip CheckInvariants (duplicate
  seq) or Compare (extra/duplicate record). Restart-only: needs a crash
  between source completion and the next run, so add the restart tier.
expected-tier: stress
tiers: default,stress,restart

diff --git a/internal/ingest/orchestrator/merge_runner.go b/internal/ingest/orchestrator/merge_runner.go
index 6118c4c..54f4981 100644
